{"word":"πούς","slug":"πούς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πούς, ποδός, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Skt.\">Skt.</a> pat, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> pes] ‘that body part which is used for walking or running’, of humans or animals <b>foot <a href='B:470 4:6'>Mt 4:6</a>; <a href='B:470 7:6'>7:6</a>; <a href='B:470 18:8'>18:8</a>; <a href='B:480 5:22'>Mk 5:22</a>; <a href='B:480 9:45'>9:45</a>; <a href='B:480 12:36'>12:36</a>; <a href='B:490 9:5'>Lk 9:5</a>; <a href='B:490 24:39'>24:39</a>; <a href='B:500 11:2'>J 11:2</a>; <a href='B:500 20:12'>20:12</a>; <a href='B:510 4:35'>Ac 4:35</a>; <a href='B:510 5:10'>5:10</a>; <a href='B:510 14:8'>14:8</a>; <a href='B:520 10:15'>Ro 10:15</a>; <a href='B:530 12:15'>1 Cor 12:15</a>; <a href='B:610 5:10'>1 Ti 5:10</a>; <a href='B:650 12:13'>Hb 12:13</a>; <a href='B:730 1:15'>Rv 1:15</a>; <a href='B:730 3:9'>3:9</a>.</b> Of a space measured by length of one’s foot, <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:βῆμα\">βῆμα</a> ποδός</el> a foot of ground <b><a href='B:510 7:5'>Ac 7:5</a>.</b> W. focus on a <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> in motion <b><a href='B:490 1:79'>Lk 1:79</a>; <a href='B:510 5:9'>Ac 5:9</a>; <a href='B:520 3:15'>Ro 3:15</a>; <a href='B:560 6:15'>Eph 6:15</a>.</b> By metonymy <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πούς\">πούς</a></el> = leg <b><a href='B:730 10:1'>Rv 10:1</a>.</b> In imagery of power and authority <b><a href='B:470 5:35'>Mt 5:35</a>; <a href='B:470 22:44'>22:44</a>; <a href='B:510 2:35'>Ac 2:35</a>; <a href='B:520 16:20'>Ro 16:20</a>; <a href='B:530 15:25'>1 Cor 15:25</a>, <a href='B:530 15:27'>27</a>; <a href='B:650 1:13'>Hb 1:13</a>; <a href='B:650 2:8'>2:8</a>; <a href='B:650 10:13'>10:13</a>; <a href='B:730 12:1'>Rv 12:1</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Πούδης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right